Gallery Doctor uses MyRoll’s Gallery Curation Engine (GCE) to automatically identify photos with bad lighting, blurry shots, poor quality pictures, or photos that we may think are not very important to you.
How do you know what a bad photo is?

Photos for review are photos that Gallery Doctor wasn’t able to identify as being bad or similar. That’s why we’re leaving it for you to decide. Gallery Doctor gets smarter based on your decisions - it learns which photos you don’t like and gets better at identifying them over time.
